issue.title: Fix Sign-In Button Misalignment - Remove Negative Positioning That Causes UI Interference
issue.body:
## Problem

The Sign-In button in the IntroScreen was misaligned due to aggressive absolute positioning that pushed it outside its container boundaries. The button used `top: -30px` which caused:

- Button floating in inconsistent positions
- Potential interference with navigation elements (tab bar/top bar)
- Layout instability across different screen states
- Poor user experience due to unpredictable button placement

## Solution

**Key Changes:**
- Changed `profileButtonContainer` positioning from `top: -30` to `top: 20` 
- Added `paddingTop: 60` to content container to accommodate button placement
- Maintained existing z-index and right alignment for accessibility

**Before:**
```tsx
profileButtonContainer: {
  position: 'absolute',
  top: -30, // ❌ Pushes button outside container bounds
  right: 16,
  zIndex: 10,
}
```

**After:**
```tsx
profileButtonContainer: {
  position: 'absolute', 
  top: 20, // ✅ Safely positioned within container
  right: 16,
  zIndex: 10,
}
```

## Validation

✅ **No layout overlaps** - Button has 40px clearance from content, 120px from screen top  
✅ **Navigation stability** - Button remains stable across all screen states (intro/scan/manual entry)  
✅ **Tab bar compatibility** - No interference with tab bar visibility toggles  
✅ **Consistent spacing** - Right margin matches content padding (16px) for visual harmony  
✅ **Proper layering** - Z-index ensures button appears above other elements  

## Impact

- Button now appears in a predictable, stable position across all devices
- No more floating or overlapping behavior with navigation elements
- Improved user experience with consistent UI spacing
- Maintains existing functionality while fixing layout issues

Fixes #162.

---

issue.title: Implement Monaco Code Editor Integration
issue.body:
This PR implements a comprehensive Monaco Editor integration for OctoPrompt, replacing basic textarea editing with a full-featured code editor that powers VS Code.

## Features Added

### 🎯 Core Monaco Integration
- **Monaco Editor Wrapper**: Custom component with OctoPrompt-specific features and theme integration
- **Monaco Diff Viewer**: Side-by-side diff comparison for AI-generated file changes
- **Lazy Loading**: Asynchronous loading with fallback components to prevent blocking page load
- **Language Detection**: Automatic syntax highlighting for 30+ programming languages

### 🚀 Enhanced File Editing
- **File Viewer Dialog**: Upgraded from basic textarea to Monaco Editor for editing mode
- **AI File Changes**: Monaco diff viewer shows proposed changes with syntax highlighting
- **Keyboard Shortcuts**: 
  - `Ctrl+S` / `Cmd+S` for save
  - `Ctrl+Shift+F` for code formatting
  - Standard Monaco shortcuts (Ctrl+/, F1, etc.)

### 🎨 UI/UX Improvements
- **Theme Integration**: Automatic dark/light mode switching based on app settings
- **Graceful Fallbacks**: Components degrade to basic functionality if Monaco fails to load
- **Performance**: Lazy loading prevents impact on initial page load
- **Error Handling**: Robust error boundaries and fallback mechanisms

### 📝 Language Support
Automatic language detection for file extensions including:
- TypeScript/JavaScript (`.ts`, `.tsx`, `.js`, `.jsx`)
- Web technologies (`.html`, `.css`, `.scss`, `.json`)
- Systems languages (`.py`, `.java`, `.cpp`, `.go`, `.rs`)
- Configuration files (`.yaml`, `.dockerfile`, `.sh`)
- And many more...

## Implementation Details

### Components Created
- `MonacoEditorWrapper`: Main editor component with shortcuts and theme integration
- `MonacoDiffViewer`: Diff viewer for code comparisons
- `LazyMonacoEditor`: Lazy-loaded editor with textarea fallback
- `LazyMonacoDiffViewer`: Lazy-loaded diff viewer with simple diff fallback
- `MonacoTestComponent`: Comprehensive test component for verification

### Integration Points
- **File Viewer Dialog**: Monaco replaces textarea in edit mode while maintaining view mode functionality
- **AI File Change Dialog**: Monaco diff viewer shows proposed changes with proper syntax highlighting

### Fallback Strategy
If Monaco Editor fails to load:
- Editor falls back to enhanced textarea with monospace font
- Diff viewer falls back to existing unified diff display
- All functionality remains available, just without advanced features

## Testing

Added `MonacoTestComponent` for comprehensive testing:
- Language switching and syntax highlighting
- Keyboard shortcuts functionality
- Theme switching behavior
- Diff viewer capabilities
- Error handling and fallbacks

## Documentation

Complete documentation added in `docs/monaco-editor-integration.md` covering:
- Architecture and component overview
- Integration guidelines
- Configuration options
- Troubleshooting guide
- Future enhancement possibilities

## Example Usage

```tsx
// Enhanced file editing
<LazyMonacoEditor
  value={fileContent}
  onChange={setFileContent}
  language="typescript"
  height="400px"
  onSave={handleSave}
/>

// AI change comparison
<LazyMonacoDiffViewer
  original={originalCode}
  modified={proposedChanges}
  language="javascript"
  height="300px"
/>
```

This implementation provides a modern, VS Code-like editing experience while maintaining backward compatibility and graceful degradation for all users.

Fixes #46.

---
